@startuml ddd-context-map
title DDD Context Map - Bounded Contexts & Relationships

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  roundCorner 12
}

rectangle "Recommendation Context\n<<Core Domain>>\n- ranking strategies (Strategy+Factory)\n- active config / deployment history\n[services/recommendation]" as REC #lightyellow

rectangle "User Profile Context\n<<Supporting>>\n- interactions, profile aggregation\n[services/user]" as USR #lightcyan

rectangle "Content Context\n<<Supporting>>\n- video catalog / candidates\n[services/content]" as CNT #lightcyan

rectangle "Dashboard / Monitoring Context\n<<Generic Subdomain>>\n- health, topology, simulator UI\n[gateway /health + React]" as DASH #whitesmoke

rectangle "API Gateway\n<<Anti-Corruption / Open Host>>\n- JWT, rate limit, breaker, routing\n[services/gateway]" as GW #lavender

USR -down-> REC : Customer / Supplier\n(profile tags upstream)
CNT -down-> REC : Customer / Supplier\n(candidate videos upstream)
REC -down-> DASH : Published Language\n(recommendation envelope: score, reason, degraded)
GW ..> REC : ACL / routing
GW ..> USR : ACL / routing
GW ..> CNT : ACL / routing
GW ..> DASH : aggregates health

note as N
  Each context owns its own database (database-per-service):
  User -> user_db (+Redis cache), Content -> content_db, Recommendation -> rec_db.
  No shared schema or cross-context DB foreign keys; integration is via HTTP only.
end note
@enduml
